# 🏠 Smart Home MCP System — Architecture Guide

## System Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["👤 User"] -->|Natural Language| B["🤖 AI Model<br/>(Claude/GPT)"]
    B -->|MCP Protocol| C["🔌 MCP Server<br/>(FastMCP)"]
    C -->|HTTP Calls| D["⚡ FastAPI<br/>Backend"]
    D -->|SQL Queries| E["🗄️ SQLite<br/>Database"]
    D -->|WebSocket| F["🖥️ Frontend<br/>(Web App)"]
    F -->|User Actions| D
```

### Core Data Flow

```
User says: "Turn on the living room lights"
    ↓
AI Model interprets intent → tool: turn_on_device(device_id=1)
    ↓
MCP Server receives tool call → HTTP POST to FastAPI
    ↓
FastAPI updates SQLite → broadcasts via WebSocket
    ↓
Frontend receives update → UI reflects new state
```

---

## 📁 Folder Structure

```
home_automation_mcp_server/
├── ai/                          # AI integration layer
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── ai_client.py            # Example AI → MCP interaction
│
├── mcp_server/                  # MCP Server (FastMCP)
│   ├── __init__.py
│   └── server.py               # Tool definitions + API mapping
│
├── backend/                     # FastAPI backend
│   ├── __init__.py
